srebrenica s doctor recounts town s living hel by laura pitte tuzla bosnia reuter neret mujanovic was a pathologiswhen he trekked through the mountains to the besieged muslitown of srebrenica last august but after treating 4 000 mangled victims of bosnia s bloodwar he considers himself a surgeon now i m a surgeon with great experience although i have nlicense to practice but if i operate on a person and he livenormally that s the greatest license a surgeon could have evacuated by the u n this week to his home town of tuzlathe muslim physician gave an eyewitness medical assessment othe horrors of the year long serb siege of srebrenica and thsuffering of the thousands trapped there i lived through hell together with the people osrebrenica all those who lived through this are the greatesheroes that humanity can produce he told reporters mujanovic 31 had practiced for two months as an assistanat a local hospital in tuzla but before going to srebrenica hhad never performed a surgical operation on his own now he sayhe has performed major surgery 1 396 times relying on books foguidance amputating arms and legs 150 times usually withouanesthetic delivering 350 babies and performing four cesareasections he worked 18 to 19 hour days slept in the hospital for thfirst 10 weeks after his arrival last aug 5 and treated 4 00patients he arrived after making the trek over mountains on foot frotuzla 60 miles northwest of srebrenica about 50 other peoplcarried in supplies and 350 soldiers guided and protected hithrough guerrilla terrain he said his worst memory was of 10 days ago when seven serb shelllanded within one minute in an area half the size of a footbalfield killing 36 people immediately and wounding 102 half othe dead were women and children the people had come out for a rare day of sunshine and thchildren were playing soccer there was no warning thblood flowed like a river in the street he said there were pieces of women all around and you could nopiece them together one wo